-- India’s Solar Capacity Rises to 979 Megawatts, Ministry Says
-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 2012-05-11T12:43:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-11/india-s-solar-capacity-rises-to-979-megawatts-ministry-says.html
India’s solar power capacity has
risen to 979 megawatts, the Ministry of New and  Renewable Energy 
said in a  statement  today.  The western state of Gujarat led installations in the
country with 655 megawatts of grid-connected solar power plants,
according to the statement.  The ministry said in December that 180 megawatts had been
built.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
 npearson7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
